public JImmutableArray<T> assign(int index,
                                          @Nullable

        Description copied from interface: JImmutableArray
        Sets the value associated with a specific index. Index must be non-null but value can be null. If the index already has a value in the map the old value is discarded and the new value is stored in its place. Returns a new JImmutableMap reflecting any changes. The original map is always left unchanged.
